metadata.name: Poe
metadata.description:
In a world of ancient wonder and delight,
A raven sits amidst a village bright
With olden charm and rustic grace, a place
That time has touched but cannot quite erase.

The bird regards the world with watchful eye
As if it knows the secrets that lie
Within the cobblestone streets and crooked lanes
That wind like streams through fields and hills and plains.

The village bustles with the sound of life,
Of farmers toiling with their fields and strife,
Of blacksmiths hammering upon the anvil,
Of children laughing with their games and thrill.

And yet, amidst this world of light and sound,
The raven sits in solemn thought profound,
A symbol of the past that lingers on
And whispers stories of the days long gone.

So let us join this bird of ancient lore
And roam the village streets like days of yore,
A place of magic, wonder, and delight
That fills our hearts with joy and with the light.
